         <abstract>
            <p>Using a method due to E. Thomas, we prove that if &lt;latex&gt;$|a| &gt; 9.9 \cdot 10^{27}$&lt;/latex&gt; then the Diophantine equations x&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; - ax&lt;sup&gt;3y&lt;/sup&gt; - x&lt;sup&gt;2y&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + axy&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; = 1 and x&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; - ax&lt;sup&gt;3y&lt;/sup&gt; - 3x&lt;sup&gt;2y&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + axy&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + y&lt;sup&gt;4&lt;/sup&gt; = ± 1 have exactly twelve solutions, namely (x, y) = (0, ± 1), (± 1, 0), (± 1, ± 1), (∓ 1, ± 1), (± a, ± 1), (± 1, ∓ a) and eight solutions, (x, y) = (0,± 1), (± 1, 0), (± 1, ± 1), (± 1, ∓ 1), respectively.</p>
          </abstract>
